
Sure, I can help you with that.

a. The sentence "Saniya played with a bird on the tree" has two meanings because the word "bird" can refer to either a specific bird or to the general concept of birds. This is an example of semantic ambiguity in NLP. Semantic ambiguity occurs when a word or phrase can have multiple meanings, depending on the context in which it is used.

b. Here are the types of NLP applications for each of the functionalities mentioned:

1) "Look ahead" typing where user is prompted with the next few words in search engines : This is a part-of-speech tagging application. Part-of-speech tagging is the process of identifying the part of speech of each word in a sentence. This information can be used to predict the next few words that a user is likely to type.
2) Grammar checker : This is a language modeling application. Language modeling is the process of predicting the next word in a sequence of words. This information can be used to identify grammatical errors in a sentence.
3) Email classification : This is a text categorization application. Text categorization is the process of classifying text into different categories. This information can be used to organize emails into different folders or to filter out spam emails.
4) Classifying entities into pre-defined labels : This is a named entity recognition application. Named entity recognition is the process of identifying and classifying named entities in a text. This information can be used to extract information from text, such as the names of people, organizations, and locations.
